1
00:00:56,090 --> 00:00:58,968
FILING FOR LOVE

2
00:01:53,772 --> 00:01:54,940
What kind of dream was that?

3
00:02:05,534 --> 00:02:06,535
<i>Did you get some rest?</i>

4
00:02:06,952 --> 00:02:09,663
<i>Don't forget to come in</i>
<i>at the usual time today. Good luck.</i>

5
00:02:09,955 --> 00:02:11,665
Oh, right. Work.

6
00:02:13,876 --> 00:02:15,836
No wonder I had that terrible dream.

7
00:02:30,976 --> 00:02:33,312
Here's your iced Americano.

8
00:02:35,189 --> 00:02:36,231
Mr. Noh.

9
00:02:36,607 --> 00:02:38,942
- Are you okay now?
- What do you mean?

10
00:02:39,026 --> 00:02:41,236
When there was a ruckus outside
two days ago

11
00:02:41,612 --> 00:02:43,530
you passed out in shock.

12
00:02:43,906 --> 00:02:47,493
The photos are everywhere.
They call you the Haemu Fainter.

13
00:02:48,535 --> 00:02:50,496
I heard the affair was real.

14
00:02:50,829 --> 00:02:52,706
So her husband is
Mr. Son from Food Brand Planning?

15
00:02:53,415 --> 00:02:55,376
What happens to them now?

16
00:02:55,584 --> 00:02:58,003
You handle the employees' affairs...

17
00:02:58,087 --> 00:02:59,380
- Da-yeong.
- Yes?

18
00:03:00,005 --> 00:03:01,715
I think your orders
are pretty backed up.

19
00:03:02,383 --> 00:03:03,801
I'm so sorry.

20
00:03:08,764 --> 00:03:10,140
Hey, Mr. Noh.

21
00:03:10,933 --> 00:03:12,017
The Haemu Fainter.

22
00:03:13,769 --> 00:03:15,854
You look fine. Are you all right now?

23
00:03:15,938 --> 00:03:17,147
- I'm fine.
- Good.

24
00:03:17,231 --> 00:03:19,858
I heard you're in charge of affairs.
How did that happen?

25
00:03:19,942 --> 00:03:21,694
- I thought you were some big shot.
- Hey.

26
00:03:22,945 --> 00:03:24,530
I handle PM cases, not affairs.

27
00:03:24,738 --> 00:03:26,490
And the term is
"personal misconduct."

28
00:03:27,324 --> 00:03:28,492
You're just clueless.

29
00:03:36,417 --> 00:03:37,668
Mr. Noh.

30
00:03:42,589 --> 00:03:43,590
Yes, Ms. Park.

31
00:03:43,882 --> 00:03:46,301
I heard what happened.
Are you all right?

32
00:03:47,302 --> 00:03:48,345
I'm fine.

33
00:03:48,887 --> 00:03:50,013
That's good to hear.

34
00:03:57,730 --> 00:03:59,356
Hey, there, Mr. Noh.

35
00:03:59,857 --> 00:04:01,066
Are you just clocking in?

36
00:04:01,442 --> 00:04:03,485
I'm so pleased to see you,
I could faint.

37
00:04:06,864 --> 00:04:07,865
Ms. Joo.

38
00:04:08,741 --> 00:04:10,534
You can't tease me about that.

39
00:04:11,410 --> 00:04:13,203
Why not? Don't I have the right?

40
00:04:13,537 --> 00:04:16,165
The only reason you're fine
without a single scratch

41
00:04:16,373 --> 00:04:19,334
is that I caught you like this
with my two arms as you fell.

42
00:04:19,752 --> 00:04:21,837
You know I saved you, right?

43
00:04:23,464 --> 00:04:25,215
I sprained my wrist a bit,
so I got some acupuncture.

44
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:28,218
Sure, I can't thank you enough.

45
00:04:28,510 --> 00:04:29,636
It's nothing, really.

46
00:04:32,014 --> 00:04:34,808
I'll type up a report on what action
to take against Mr. Son.

47
00:04:35,559 --> 00:04:37,186
I took care of that already.

48
00:04:37,811 --> 00:04:38,854
What?

49
00:04:39,855 --> 00:04:41,190
I closed that case.

50
00:04:44,860 --> 00:04:47,029
Mouthwatering and mellow,
here's Masigo.

51
00:04:47,446 --> 00:04:50,282
With Haemu's own
innovative food technology

52
00:04:50,365 --> 00:04:53,660
Masigo succeeded to realize
the farm-to-table notion

53
00:04:53,744 --> 00:04:55,287
and we're confident it will become

54
00:04:55,370 --> 00:04:58,207
a brand that represents Haemu
and leads global food trends.

55
00:04:58,499 --> 00:05:00,667
That concludes the presentation.
Thanks for listening.

56
00:05:05,172 --> 00:05:06,215
Thank you.

57
00:05:12,679 --> 00:05:13,722
Thank you.

58
00:05:14,014 --> 00:05:15,349
I'll do my best.

59
00:05:20,562 --> 00:05:22,773
<i>Even so, that's not right, Ms. Joo.</i>

60
00:05:23,774 --> 00:05:26,819
How could Ms. Jeong be demoted
to a plant while Mr. Son remains?

61
00:05:27,027 --> 00:05:28,695
And he gets to keep his project?

62
00:05:29,780 --> 00:05:32,574
If we must decide who did worse,
Ms. Jeong is single

63
00:05:32,658 --> 00:05:34,326
while Mr. Son's married,
so he did more harm.

64
00:05:34,409 --> 00:05:36,245
Who did Mr. Son cause harm to?

65
00:05:37,496 --> 00:05:39,331
Mr. Son always did well at work

66
00:05:39,414 --> 00:05:41,625
and he's in charge of a new brand
the Food Team has invested in.

67
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:43,210
What about Ms. Jeong?

68
00:05:43,293 --> 00:05:45,045
All she did was play a part
in Mr. Son's project.

69
00:05:45,128 --> 00:05:46,588
Her performance and reputation
are below his.

70
00:05:47,464 --> 00:05:48,757
From the company's point of view

71
00:05:48,841 --> 00:05:51,176
Ms. Jeong has done more harm
than Mr. Son.

72
00:05:51,760 --> 00:05:52,803
Am I wrong?

73
00:05:54,388 --> 00:05:55,597
Still, morally speaking...

74
00:06:00,394 --> 00:06:01,436
Morals?

75
00:06:01,979 --> 00:06:03,856
Do you think
you're a police officer or a judge?

76
00:06:04,147 --> 00:06:06,942
Do companies reward the good
and punish the bad?

77
00:06:07,234 --> 00:06:09,361
A company only has to care

78
00:06:09,444 --> 00:06:11,905
about the profit or loss
caused by an employee.

79
00:06:11,989 --> 00:06:14,825
Because here,
that is our ethics and morals.

80
00:06:24,251 --> 00:06:25,335
What is it?

81
00:06:25,419 --> 00:06:27,421
Did you hope
for an exhilarating resolution?

82
00:06:27,921 --> 00:06:30,591
For a cheating couple
to be humiliated out of their jobs?

83
00:06:33,176 --> 00:06:34,720
You're more naive than you look.

84
00:06:36,430 --> 00:06:37,723
Why did you put me in charge?

85
00:06:41,018 --> 00:06:42,060
This duty

86
00:06:43,395 --> 00:06:45,272
doesn't suit me because I'm naive.

87
00:06:51,445 --> 00:06:52,571
No, you're perfect for the job.

88
00:06:52,654 --> 00:06:55,032
- Ms. Joo, what on earth...
- Don't get too upset.

89
00:06:55,115 --> 00:06:57,159
Mr. Son got a bigger percentage
of his pay docked.

90
00:06:57,534 --> 00:07:00,412
Not to mention that this incident
ruined his reputation for good.

91
00:07:00,495 --> 00:07:02,998
It will be taken into consideration
at his next performance review.

92
00:07:03,498 --> 00:07:06,001
Plus, there are legal repercussions
if he's sued for divorce.

93
00:07:08,211 --> 00:07:10,589
There, let's forget
about a closed case.

94
00:07:10,672 --> 00:07:12,257
Do your next assignment right.

95
00:07:12,466 --> 00:07:13,467
Sorry?

96
00:07:17,012 --> 00:07:18,013
"Work.com."

97
00:07:18,513 --> 00:07:20,265
You should check it out.
The comments are insane.

98
00:07:50,128 --> 00:07:54,800
EPISODE 2:
I AM THE BEST

99
00:07:55,384 --> 00:07:57,511
<i>Seriously, do something about Zone F.</i>

100
00:07:57,594 --> 00:07:59,262
<i>It's basically a love motel in Haemu.</i>

101
00:07:59,596 --> 00:08:01,473
<i>- It's like watching porn.</i>
- "Zone F"?

102
00:08:01,556 --> 00:08:02,641
<i>So everyone knows it.</i>

103
00:08:02,975 --> 00:08:04,559
<i>The head office's</i>
<i>basement parking lot.</i>

104
00:08:05,143 --> 00:08:07,854
<i>- It probably has no cameras.</i>
- What is this about?

105
00:08:07,938 --> 00:08:09,231
<i>I never park there.</i>

106
00:08:09,314 --> 00:08:10,691
Is this news to you?

107
00:08:11,942 --> 00:08:14,403
It's Zone F in level four
of the basement parking lot.

108
00:08:15,070 --> 00:08:17,072
It's the spot
for couples in the company

109
00:08:17,155 --> 00:08:19,032
whether they're dating
morally or immorally.

110
00:08:19,574 --> 00:08:22,452
It's dark with no cameras
pointing that way

111
00:08:22,703 --> 00:08:24,246
and not many park that far down.

112
00:08:24,663 --> 00:08:25,747
It's perfect.

113
00:08:25,998 --> 00:08:28,083
You seem to know a lot, Mr. Cha.

114
00:08:28,166 --> 00:08:30,711
That's what I heard
through the grapevine.

115
00:08:31,586 --> 00:08:33,046
Let's check the facts first.

116
00:08:33,505 --> 00:08:35,424
We can't investigate
based on a rumor.

117
00:08:35,507 --> 00:08:36,633
- Yes, sir.
- Okay?

118
00:08:36,717 --> 00:08:38,343
Check facts? With whom?

119
00:08:39,136 --> 00:08:40,762
Our team has set up

120
00:08:40,846 --> 00:08:43,306
- a humint network.
- What? "Humint"?

121
00:08:43,390 --> 00:08:44,433
INFO GATHERED FROM INFORMANTS

122
00:08:44,516 --> 00:08:47,227
- Yes.
<i>- Gosh, don't even talk about it.</i>

123
00:08:47,310 --> 00:08:48,520
<i>There's no end to it.</i>

124
00:08:48,603 --> 00:08:51,481
<i>It's embarrassing for both parties</i>
<i>if we catch them in the act.</i>

125
00:08:52,024 --> 00:08:53,525
<i>We just turn a blind eye.</i>

126
00:08:53,608 --> 00:08:56,695
<i>I heard Zone F is the place to go.</i>

127
00:08:56,778 --> 00:08:59,906
BASEMENT PARKING CLOSED
FOR REPAIR WORK

128
00:08:59,990 --> 00:09:01,033
It's that spot over there.

129
00:09:01,908 --> 00:09:04,036
Is it more thrilling
if they do it there?

130
00:09:04,578 --> 00:09:07,039
I don't know why people
with decent jobs would do that.

131
00:09:09,082 --> 00:09:10,375
I wonder myself.

132
00:09:10,459 --> 00:09:12,627
If you see anything suspicious

133
00:09:12,711 --> 00:09:14,004
please report it to us.

134
00:09:14,087 --> 00:09:16,923
- Sure thing. Take care, then.
- Thank you.

135
00:09:19,760 --> 00:09:23,346
Our humint network confirmed
the rumor is true.

136
00:09:27,100 --> 00:09:28,685
Humint, my foot.

137
00:09:30,687 --> 00:09:32,564
- Let's go eat.
- Okay.

138
00:09:32,647 --> 00:09:35,275
The cafeteria's serving pork cutlet,
<i>doenjang </i>soup

139
00:09:35,358 --> 00:09:36,443
- braised potatoes...
- Not there.

140
00:09:36,526 --> 00:09:38,653
I'll check my list
of nearby restaurants.

141
00:09:39,029 --> 00:09:40,280
Don't bother.

142
00:09:45,202 --> 00:09:47,746
THIS EVENING

143
00:09:52,459 --> 00:09:54,127
What are you doing today?
It's your birthday.

144
00:09:54,795 --> 00:09:55,921
Did your boyfriend schedule a date?

145
00:09:56,755 --> 00:09:57,756
Well...

146
00:09:57,839 --> 00:09:59,966
Why are you so mysterious?

147
00:10:00,217 --> 00:10:03,053
I'm curious what kind of guy
girls like you date.

148
00:10:41,216 --> 00:10:43,552
Why does the cafeteria food
get worse by the day?

149
00:10:43,718 --> 00:10:46,138
- Right? Let's eat out tomorrow.
- Okay.

150
00:10:46,429 --> 00:10:47,889
- Ms. Yeon.
- What?

151
00:10:47,973 --> 00:10:50,392
Isn't that Mr. Kwon, your husband?

152
00:10:51,059 --> 00:10:52,269
Yes, that's right.

153
00:10:52,352 --> 00:10:54,062
Why don't you even say hi?

154
00:10:54,855 --> 00:10:55,981
Did you two fight?

155
00:10:57,357 --> 00:10:59,109
We didn't fight. We get along fine.

156
00:10:59,442 --> 00:11:01,528
Ji-yeon, wait until you get married.

157
00:11:01,611 --> 00:11:02,654
After just a few years

158
00:11:02,904 --> 00:11:04,531
you flinch
when your hands accidentally touch.

159
00:11:05,031 --> 00:11:06,074
That's an exaggeration.

160
00:11:09,744 --> 00:11:11,037
You two are hilarious.

161
00:11:11,371 --> 00:11:13,582
Before you got married,
you didn't say hi

162
00:11:13,665 --> 00:11:15,000
because you were dating in secret.

163
00:11:15,083 --> 00:11:16,751
But now,
everyone knows you're married.

164
00:11:17,294 --> 00:11:18,587
Are you shy now that you're married?

165
00:11:18,670 --> 00:11:20,213
We're keeping work
and personal lives separate.

166
00:11:20,964 --> 00:11:24,259
You speak as if
your private life is pretty eventful.

167
00:11:27,095 --> 00:11:28,096
Hey.

168
00:11:29,055 --> 00:11:30,098
Do you guys even do it?

169
00:11:30,599 --> 00:11:31,600
Stop it.

170
00:11:32,517 --> 00:11:33,977
You don't do that with family.

171
00:11:35,896 --> 00:11:37,314
You used to be so fired up.

172
00:11:38,106 --> 00:11:39,816
Why does it die
once people get married?

173
00:11:40,275 --> 00:11:42,319
You burn to death
if you stay fired up.

174
00:11:51,119 --> 00:11:52,787
NEW MESSAGE FROM YEON
FROM GENERAL AFFAIRS

175
00:11:54,122 --> 00:11:56,249
<i>I'm meeting old friends from school</i>
<i>and will be home late.</i>

176
00:11:57,709 --> 00:11:58,793
<i>Okay.</i>

177
00:12:13,808 --> 00:12:15,644
Oh, dear. I'm so sorry, Mr. Kwon.

178
00:12:16,311 --> 00:12:19,022
- It's okay.
- I'm so stupid.

179
00:12:19,105 --> 00:12:20,857
I'm really sorry.

180
00:12:20,941 --> 00:12:22,692
Don't be. It happens.

181
00:12:24,027 --> 00:12:25,028
Ms. Seon?

182
00:12:25,570 --> 00:12:26,738
I'm coming, sir.

183
00:12:27,280 --> 00:12:28,448
- Sorry.
- Go ahead.

184
00:12:51,304 --> 00:12:53,098
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

185
00:12:58,061 --> 00:12:59,604
I'm loving this.

186
00:13:00,105 --> 00:13:01,231
- Right?
- Jun-seo!

187
00:13:01,898 --> 00:13:04,192
- Over here.
- He looks even better now.

188
00:13:04,276 --> 00:13:06,319
- Long time no see.
- You haven't changed at all.

189
00:13:06,528 --> 00:13:09,239
Sorry, I forgot to tell you
he was coming.

190
00:13:10,782 --> 00:13:11,825
Don't worry.

191
00:13:12,075 --> 00:13:13,785
It's been ages since we broke up.

192
00:13:22,168 --> 00:13:23,628
It has been a while, So-young.

193
00:13:23,962 --> 00:13:25,005
Yes.

194
00:13:25,213 --> 00:13:27,048
You look just the same.

195
00:13:27,716 --> 00:13:28,758
You haven't changed.

196
00:13:30,051 --> 00:13:32,345
I'm not the same. I got old, right?

197
00:13:32,429 --> 00:13:33,513
No.

198
00:13:33,847 --> 00:13:35,598
You're pretty. Just like before.

199
00:13:36,725 --> 00:13:39,144
- What's going on here?
- You're prettier now.

200
00:13:39,936 --> 00:13:42,147
- You're just the same.
- I lost my appetite.

201
00:13:42,981 --> 00:13:44,566
- Sorry.
- Pour me a drink?

202
00:13:45,066 --> 00:13:46,109
Here.

203
00:13:47,777 --> 00:13:48,903
<i>Let's begin.</i>

204
00:13:54,993 --> 00:13:56,453
<i>You can vote now.</i>

205
00:13:56,536 --> 00:13:58,038
FINAL RESULT
OF THE THIRD SURVIVOR

206
00:13:59,039 --> 00:14:00,248
Why did his ranking drop?

207
00:14:00,332 --> 00:14:03,251
<i>Vote for the person</i>
<i>who stole your heart.</i>

208
00:14:05,170 --> 00:14:07,005
The mission benefit is too great.

209
00:14:07,088 --> 00:14:10,633
<i>BOYS II PLANET's first round</i>
<i>of the final global vote is now open.</i>

210
00:14:11,509 --> 00:14:13,178
<i>BOYS II PLANET's final global...</i>

211
00:14:13,261 --> 00:14:14,971
Can I vote for the same person twice?

212
00:14:15,055 --> 00:14:16,765
<i>Log onto the BOYS II PLANET site</i>

213
00:14:17,724 --> 00:14:18,892
<i>and click "vote"</i>

214
00:14:19,434 --> 00:14:21,561
<i>- then select one participant.</i>
- Who's that?

215
00:14:26,691 --> 00:14:28,985
Hi. Let's have a drink.
It's been a while.

216
00:14:41,498 --> 00:14:43,833
What are you up to?
Do you want to get back with me?

217
00:14:45,335 --> 00:14:46,419
Do you want to?

218
00:14:47,504 --> 00:14:48,630
Forget it, then.

219
00:14:49,798 --> 00:14:52,717
Gosh.
You're really one-sidedly one-sided.

220
00:14:53,343 --> 00:14:55,678
You asked me out
then suddenly ghosted me.

221
00:14:56,304 --> 00:14:58,181
Now you barge in after two years

222
00:14:58,556 --> 00:15:00,183
- and want a drink?
- So what?

223
00:15:00,767 --> 00:15:02,310
Were you sad that I dumped you?

224
00:15:03,144 --> 00:15:04,354
Did you cry over me?

225
00:15:05,230 --> 00:15:06,523
You didn't.

226
00:15:06,606 --> 00:15:09,067
"If you want to leave, go ahead.
I won't hold you back."

227
00:15:09,651 --> 00:15:11,945
I bet you didn't even shed a tear.

228
00:15:12,779 --> 00:15:14,280
Here. have a drink and call it even.

229
00:15:26,042 --> 00:15:27,043
It's good, isn't it?

230
00:15:29,337 --> 00:15:30,505
It's not bad.

231
00:15:32,298 --> 00:15:33,967
Let me stay for a while.

232
00:15:35,468 --> 00:15:37,262
- What?
- Let me stay here.

233
00:15:38,054 --> 00:15:39,347
The whiskey's the rent.

234
00:15:39,764 --> 00:15:41,099
This costs over three million won.

235
00:15:41,182 --> 00:15:43,351
Hey, what kind of nonsense is this?

236
00:15:43,852 --> 00:15:45,895
Get out. This isn't a boarding house.

237
00:15:45,979 --> 00:15:47,814
I really don't have a place to go.

238
00:15:48,064 --> 00:15:51,526
I had to leave my old place
and I couldn't find a new place yet.

239
00:15:51,818 --> 00:15:53,278
You know that my family...

240
00:15:54,279 --> 00:15:55,947
They're no help to me at all.

241
00:15:57,657 --> 00:15:59,200
I get that you're in a tough spot...

242
00:15:59,451 --> 00:16:02,078
You can't barge
into a guy's bachelor pad.

243
00:16:04,956 --> 00:16:06,749
- I'll get you a hotel room.
- For how long?

244
00:16:07,167 --> 00:16:08,710
Who knows how long I'll need?

245
00:16:09,252 --> 00:16:10,378
Do you have ten million won?

246
00:16:15,884 --> 00:16:17,635
I guess you can't help me.

247
00:16:18,303 --> 00:16:19,929
I get it. I'll leave.

248
00:16:20,805 --> 00:16:24,434
I'll stay at a sauna
or end up on some street corner.

249
00:16:24,517 --> 00:16:27,228
And if a creepy guy hits on me?

250
00:16:27,312 --> 00:16:29,230
I'll go with him. I can't be picky.

251
00:16:30,565 --> 00:16:31,608
Goodbye.

252
00:16:42,577 --> 00:16:43,661
It's only for the time being.

253
00:16:44,329 --> 00:16:45,747
Leave as soon as you can.

254
00:16:49,667 --> 00:16:52,128
I'll take the small room.
You can take the big room.

255
00:16:56,674 --> 00:16:59,177
Wait, isn't that a given?

256
00:17:02,388 --> 00:17:04,015
How brazen.

257
00:17:11,022 --> 00:17:13,107
Take a look at the shower head.
It's leaking again.

258
00:17:14,526 --> 00:17:15,652
Okay, I will.

259
00:17:17,820 --> 00:17:19,322
You say that and do nothing.

260
00:17:20,698 --> 00:17:21,741
Goodness.

261
00:17:22,534 --> 00:17:25,828
Did you read about Zone F online?

262
00:17:27,580 --> 00:17:29,040
Yes, I did.

263
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:32,585
Some people have too much energy.

264
00:17:33,169 --> 00:17:35,922
They do something at work
that we don't even do in bed.

265
00:17:53,773 --> 00:17:54,816
Shall we do it?

266
00:17:59,904 --> 00:18:01,406
I'm tired.

267
00:18:06,119 --> 00:18:07,704
I wasn't interested, either.

268
00:18:09,122 --> 00:18:10,164
Turn off the light.

269
00:18:10,498 --> 00:18:11,749
You do it.

270
00:18:28,725 --> 00:18:31,060
You've lost weight.
Your face got smaller.

271
00:18:32,228 --> 00:18:34,230
Are you stressed out
because of Joo In-a?

272
00:18:36,232 --> 00:18:37,900
Drink the whiskey you brought.

273
00:18:37,984 --> 00:18:39,152
Don't touch my beer.

274
00:18:40,570 --> 00:18:42,113
Do you hate her that much?

275
00:18:43,531 --> 00:18:44,574
Why?

276
00:18:44,866 --> 00:18:46,326
Because she made you handle affairs?

277
00:18:46,409 --> 00:18:48,202
They're PM cases, not affairs.

278
00:18:49,120 --> 00:18:51,706
Ms. Joo doesn't know about me yet.

279
00:18:51,789 --> 00:18:53,666
I was working on something
on Team One.

280
00:18:54,375 --> 00:18:57,128
I put everything in the folder
and when she sees that

281
00:18:58,421 --> 00:19:00,423
she'll see how good I am
and reappoint me.

282
00:19:00,506 --> 00:19:01,674
If she's that competent.

283
00:19:03,718 --> 00:19:04,802
Think about it.

284
00:19:05,094 --> 00:19:07,805
She wouldn't want to waste
talent like mine on stupid cases.

285
00:19:07,889 --> 00:19:10,266
Why not? I think
you're perfect for the job.

286
00:19:10,808 --> 00:19:12,393
To handle the PM cheaters.

287
00:19:12,477 --> 00:19:13,853
Why me?

288
00:19:16,314 --> 00:19:17,774
- Hang on.
<i>- You are</i>

289
00:19:18,107 --> 00:19:19,484
the best one for the job.

290
00:19:22,612 --> 00:19:23,655
Hey.

291
00:19:24,947 --> 00:19:27,241
That's exactly what Joo In-a said,
that I was the best for the job.

292
00:19:28,242 --> 00:19:30,787
- Why am I best for the job?
- It's about couples in love.

293
00:19:31,496 --> 00:19:34,499
- That's your expertise.
- What does she know about me?

294
00:19:35,333 --> 00:19:37,377
We just met. She can't know...

295
00:19:39,587 --> 00:19:40,630
No way.

296
00:19:41,381 --> 00:19:42,465
That retreating figure...

297
00:19:46,969 --> 00:19:48,096
Did she see me?

298
00:19:50,932 --> 00:19:52,809
So the reason she chose me...

299
00:19:54,811 --> 00:19:55,853
was that?

300
00:19:58,815 --> 00:20:00,566
<i>No, it can't be.</i>

301
00:20:02,610 --> 00:20:03,653
<i>Can it be?</i>

302
00:20:05,488 --> 00:20:06,489
<i>Is it?</i>

303
00:20:08,199 --> 00:20:09,367
<i>Long, straight hair.</i>

304
00:20:10,660 --> 00:20:11,786
<i>A white shirt.</i>

305
00:20:19,669 --> 00:20:20,920
It's practically a uniform.

306
00:20:40,106 --> 00:20:41,190
<i>I can't say for sure.</i>

307
00:20:42,400 --> 00:20:43,568
<i>I don't think it was her.</i>

308
00:20:51,409 --> 00:20:52,744
Why were you staring at me?

309
00:20:54,036 --> 00:20:55,288
Is a ghost haunting me?

310
00:20:55,371 --> 00:20:56,748
I came to make myself some coffee.

311
00:20:59,375 --> 00:21:01,711
You look like
you have something to say.

312
00:21:02,044 --> 00:21:03,171
Mr. Noh.

313
00:21:03,254 --> 00:21:05,673
If you have any concerns,
you can come to me freely.

314
00:21:07,216 --> 00:21:09,427
<i>Yes, rather than driving myself crazy</i>

315
00:21:09,510 --> 00:21:10,678
<i>I'll ask her and clear the air.</i>

316
00:21:11,220 --> 00:21:12,930
- Ms. Joo.
<i>- Wait.</i>

317
00:21:15,475 --> 00:21:17,685
<i>I can't ask if she saw me kiss.</i>

318
00:21:19,604 --> 00:21:20,605
What is it?

319
00:21:22,273 --> 00:21:23,900
What should we do
about the basement parking lot?

320
00:21:23,983 --> 00:21:27,570
We've confirmed through our humint
that it's a real issue.

321
00:21:27,945 --> 00:21:30,490
Shall we put up a sign saying
personal misconduct isn't allowed?

322
00:21:30,573 --> 00:21:31,783
We can't say we did any work, then.

323
00:21:32,325 --> 00:21:34,535
- We have to expose them.
- Expose?

324
00:21:34,744 --> 00:21:36,537
How am I going to do that?

325
00:21:36,621 --> 00:21:38,331
I can't go on a stakeout
just to wait for it.

326
00:21:38,414 --> 00:21:39,415
A stakeout?

327
00:21:39,749 --> 00:21:41,000
A stakeout?

328
00:21:41,334 --> 00:21:43,795
Why would you say something
so nonsensical?

329
00:21:43,878 --> 00:21:47,089
We're not detectives.
Why would we go on a stakeout?

330
00:21:47,882 --> 00:21:49,967
- Right, exactly.
- Exactly.

331
00:21:50,301 --> 00:21:52,303
I heard that someone
on the Audit Team

332
00:21:52,386 --> 00:21:54,722
flew a drone and took photos.

333
00:21:55,056 --> 00:21:58,976
How could an auditor do that?
We're not some drone-flying club.

334
00:22:04,774 --> 00:22:06,192
Down your coffee and get moving.

335
00:22:07,318 --> 00:22:08,694
My poor legs.

336
00:22:11,113 --> 00:22:14,575
This was the only company car
left for us to take.

337
00:22:15,660 --> 00:22:18,287
Darn it. I should've brought my car.

338
00:22:18,746 --> 00:22:21,249
Still, if you push the seat
back a bit

339
00:22:21,332 --> 00:22:22,542
it should free up some space.

340
00:22:22,625 --> 00:22:24,377
- No, it's fine.
- Let me help you.

341
00:22:24,669 --> 00:22:26,212
It's fine, really. I...

342
00:22:29,799 --> 00:22:31,425
I'm so sorry, Mr. Noh.

343
00:22:48,109 --> 00:22:49,986
Jeez, what the heck
are we even doing?

344
00:22:50,987 --> 00:22:52,655
Okay, Hyun-kyu.

345
00:22:53,030 --> 00:22:56,200
You didn't do all that studying
for your degree

346
00:22:56,993 --> 00:22:58,828
just to do this kind of job, did you?

347
00:23:00,454 --> 00:23:03,958
Unlike you,
I didn't go to a good university

348
00:23:04,041 --> 00:23:05,793
nor have great credentials.

349
00:23:06,919 --> 00:23:08,671
I barely got this job
because I'm from the area

350
00:23:08,754 --> 00:23:10,214
where Haemu built a huge factory.

351
00:23:10,673 --> 00:23:12,341
Oh, during my interview I said

352
00:23:13,092 --> 00:23:14,635
"White blood runs through my veins."

353
00:23:15,928 --> 00:23:18,306
That's how I introduced myself,
and they liked how I was different.

354
00:23:20,808 --> 00:23:22,935
- "White blood."
- White blood.

355
00:23:24,437 --> 00:23:26,147
- By white, you meant Haemu's color?
- Yes.

356
00:23:26,772 --> 00:23:28,566
That's why they call you
"White Blood Cell."

357
00:23:28,649 --> 00:23:29,650
That's right.

358
00:23:33,195 --> 00:23:36,949
You know, competent people like you

359
00:23:37,033 --> 00:23:39,994
might feel bored
by what our team does.

360
00:23:40,077 --> 00:23:43,247
But working at Haemu
which everyone envies

361
00:23:43,331 --> 00:23:47,919
and being on the Audit Team,
the best team in the company

362
00:23:48,210 --> 00:23:50,338
makes me pleased and proud.

363
00:24:04,602 --> 00:24:05,811
Hey, White Blood Cell.

364
00:24:06,228 --> 00:24:07,271
Yes, Mr. Noh?

365
00:24:08,022 --> 00:24:10,524
I didn't doze off.
I was only blinking for a long time.

366
00:24:10,608 --> 00:24:11,651
Do you remember

367
00:24:12,318 --> 00:24:13,819
the day Ms. Joo first joined?

368
00:24:18,491 --> 00:24:20,826
Do you know what she was wearing?

369
00:24:21,786 --> 00:24:23,079
Just a moment.

370
00:24:23,621 --> 00:24:26,415
- I remember such details perfectly.
- Do you?

371
00:24:27,667 --> 00:24:29,043
See if you can remember.

372
00:24:30,628 --> 00:24:31,629
What was she wearing?

373
00:24:32,964 --> 00:24:34,090
She wore

374
00:24:36,050 --> 00:24:37,218
black pants.

375
00:24:39,595 --> 00:24:41,639
What about her top?

376
00:24:42,098 --> 00:24:43,140
Her top...

377
00:24:44,684 --> 00:24:45,726
It was black.

378
00:24:47,186 --> 00:24:48,479
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

379
00:24:51,107 --> 00:24:52,149
It was black.

380
00:24:55,361 --> 00:24:56,404
Or not.

381
00:24:57,822 --> 00:24:59,407
I think it was a white shirt.

382
00:25:00,658 --> 00:25:01,659
Hey.

383
00:25:03,077 --> 00:25:04,078
Are you saying she wore white?

384
00:25:06,205 --> 00:25:07,289
Maybe not.

385
00:25:07,832 --> 00:25:09,667
- What?
- Was it black?

386
00:25:10,584 --> 00:25:12,628
- Was it black?
- No.

387
00:25:13,713 --> 00:25:14,755
It was white.

388
00:25:15,339 --> 00:25:16,382
Yes, white.

389
00:25:17,466 --> 00:25:18,592
Why, you!

390
00:25:21,012 --> 00:25:22,054
It was definitely white.

391
00:25:23,472 --> 00:25:24,557
Am I mistaken?

392
00:25:25,725 --> 00:25:27,059
Forget I even asked.

393
00:25:27,852 --> 00:25:30,938
- I'll go get coffee, so sober up.
- Okay.

394
00:25:59,133 --> 00:26:01,343
I have a bad feeling about this.

395
00:26:04,722 --> 00:26:06,474
Gosh, what am I even doing?

396
00:26:07,516 --> 00:26:09,852
So what if she saw it? I don't care.

397
00:26:10,311 --> 00:26:13,355
It's not like I committed a crime.
Forget it.

398
00:26:14,315 --> 00:26:15,357
Oh, my gosh.

399
00:26:17,818 --> 00:26:19,070
Why are you so startled?

400
00:26:22,573 --> 00:26:23,949
You walked in so suddenly.

401
00:26:25,910 --> 00:26:27,745
Can't I walk in suddenly?

402
00:26:28,329 --> 00:26:29,997
Should I have knocked?

403
00:26:32,875 --> 00:26:33,959
What?

404
00:26:34,543 --> 00:26:35,544
Were you

405
00:26:37,671 --> 00:26:38,839
doing this again?

406
00:26:57,441 --> 00:26:58,526
What was that?

407
00:27:00,694 --> 00:27:03,239
So she saw it. She saw everything.

408
00:27:42,570 --> 00:27:43,612
Noh Ki-jun.

409
00:27:45,364 --> 00:27:46,448
What do you want?

410
00:27:46,991 --> 00:27:48,492
You told me to ignore you at work.

411
00:27:48,576 --> 00:27:50,035
It's just us now.

412
00:27:50,703 --> 00:27:52,329
Is it Joo In-a again?

413
00:27:52,621 --> 00:27:53,747
You look half-dead.

414
00:27:53,831 --> 00:27:54,832
Yes.

415
00:27:55,374 --> 00:27:57,168
Bury me on a sunny slope.

416
00:27:58,127 --> 00:27:59,587
Why are you thinking
of getting buried?

417
00:28:00,212 --> 00:28:01,505
You have a lifeline.

418
00:28:02,047 --> 00:28:03,132
Director Kim.

419
00:28:04,008 --> 00:28:06,177
His dinner with the VP got canceled

420
00:28:06,260 --> 00:28:07,887
and he seemed to be looking
for a drinking buddy.

421
00:28:24,445 --> 00:28:25,738
Hello, Director Kim.

422
00:28:26,488 --> 00:28:28,657
It's Assistant Manager Noh Ki-jun.

423
00:28:36,373 --> 00:28:41,086
Ms. Joo talks back
to every senior executive.

424
00:28:41,337 --> 00:28:43,923
Does she think I'm staying still
because I can't speak up?

425
00:28:44,340 --> 00:28:47,218
- I'm just keeping my boundaries.
- Yes, you're right.

426
00:28:48,219 --> 00:28:49,803
Is she rude to the executives, too?

427
00:28:50,638 --> 00:28:53,807
I guess she's not the type
to bow to the powerful.

428
00:28:53,891 --> 00:28:58,479
I don't care how she treats
the powerful or powerless.

429
00:28:59,647 --> 00:29:00,731
And there's you.

430
00:29:00,814 --> 00:29:03,192
She has such
a poor judgment of character.

431
00:29:03,651 --> 00:29:06,654
You're our ace, Mr. Noh.

432
00:29:06,737 --> 00:29:08,697
Yet she dumped you in Team Three.

433
00:29:09,114 --> 00:29:12,076
Now, you're handling PM cases.
What the heck is PM, anyway?

434
00:29:12,159 --> 00:29:13,160
Exactly.

435
00:29:13,827 --> 00:29:15,788
I'm having the worst time, sir.

436
00:29:16,121 --> 00:29:18,874
Don't you worry about that.

437
00:29:19,792 --> 00:29:20,793
You know who I am.

438
00:29:21,794 --> 00:29:24,088
Let me tell you something

439
00:29:24,546 --> 00:29:26,465
that's still off the record.

440
00:29:32,554 --> 00:29:35,683
I'm working to create
a new department.

441
00:29:37,101 --> 00:29:43,732
It'll serve as the control tower
of the whole organization.

442
00:29:44,733 --> 00:29:47,027
Business General... No.

443
00:29:47,111 --> 00:29:50,155
It's called
the General Business Control HQ.

444
00:29:50,239 --> 00:29:52,866
General Business Control HQ.

445
00:29:54,201 --> 00:29:56,036
- What a great name.
- Right?

446
00:29:57,705 --> 00:29:59,832
I said I wanted you on the team.

447
00:30:00,666 --> 00:30:03,460
You'll be able to escape soon.

448
00:30:07,923 --> 00:30:10,175
- Let me pour you a drink, sir.
- Okay.

449
00:30:13,095 --> 00:30:14,722
A toast

450
00:30:15,389 --> 00:30:18,309
to our General Business

451
00:30:18,392 --> 00:30:20,519
- Control HQ.
- Control HQ.

452
00:30:20,686 --> 00:30:24,023
- Let's drink to its bright future.
- Cheers!

453
00:30:33,240 --> 00:30:34,450
I'm in the mood.

454
00:30:48,672 --> 00:30:49,757
I'm heading home.

455
00:30:49,840 --> 00:30:51,425
Bye. See you tomorrow.

456
00:30:55,346 --> 00:30:57,598
IT DEVELOPMENT TEAM
ASSISTANT MANAGER KWON HYUN-WOO

457
00:30:57,681 --> 00:30:59,016
<i>It's raining.</i>

458
00:30:59,099 --> 00:31:00,142
<i>When do you get off work?</i>

459
00:31:03,729 --> 00:31:04,772
<i>I'm working late.</i>

460
00:31:05,147 --> 00:31:06,440
<i>Buy an umbrella and head home.</i>

461
00:31:25,584 --> 00:31:26,752
Hello?

462
00:31:30,631 --> 00:31:31,632
Jun-seo?

463
00:31:33,926 --> 00:31:35,386
We did that all the time.

464
00:31:36,345 --> 00:31:37,471
Back then...

465
00:31:38,764 --> 00:31:40,057
we were young and rash.

466
00:31:40,641 --> 00:31:41,809
I'm glad I called you.

467
00:31:50,067 --> 00:31:52,027
Are you sure
you don't need to eat dinner?

468
00:31:52,486 --> 00:31:54,238
You love to eat.

469
00:31:54,947 --> 00:31:56,698
I'm okay with anything
if I'm with you.

470
00:32:01,036 --> 00:32:02,079
Right.

471
00:32:07,167 --> 00:32:08,544
It's pouring.

472
00:32:17,678 --> 00:32:19,346
- Why don't we...
- Yes?

473
00:32:20,013 --> 00:32:21,056
stay together?

474
00:32:22,266 --> 00:32:23,517
Just until the rain stops.

475
00:32:53,839 --> 00:32:55,174
SEND
IT DEVELOPMENT TEAM, KWON HYUN-WOO

476
00:32:58,177 --> 00:32:59,344
Sent.

477
00:33:01,054 --> 00:33:02,389
Great work.

478
00:33:02,723 --> 00:33:04,141
My gosh. You must be tired.

479
00:33:04,391 --> 00:33:05,517
Great work until late.

480
00:33:05,601 --> 00:33:07,978
Don't mention it. I'm feeling proud.

481
00:33:08,395 --> 00:33:10,063
Today was
the first overtime of my life.

482
00:33:10,981 --> 00:33:11,982
Really?

483
00:33:12,608 --> 00:33:13,650
In that case

484
00:33:14,151 --> 00:33:15,402
why don't we grab a drink
to celebrate?

485
00:33:15,486 --> 00:33:16,778
I'd love to.

486
00:33:17,070 --> 00:33:18,363
Let's eat
something delicious, Mr. Kwon.

487
00:33:18,447 --> 00:33:20,365
- Okay, let's wrap up and leave.
- Great!

488
00:33:29,249 --> 00:33:30,584
WIFE

489
00:33:41,261 --> 00:33:42,638
I said you could leave first.

490
00:33:46,225 --> 00:33:47,267
Were you rained on?

491
00:33:54,233 --> 00:33:55,484
We shouldn't do this.

492
00:34:00,739 --> 00:34:02,157
The rain has stopped.

493
00:34:04,451 --> 00:34:05,452
Let's do it.

494
00:34:05,994 --> 00:34:07,579
- What?
- Let's do it.

495
00:34:09,039 --> 00:34:10,541
We can't keep going like this.
We have to do it.

496
00:34:11,166 --> 00:34:12,376
What's with you?

497
00:34:15,087 --> 00:34:17,381
All right. Let's go home first.
You're going to catch a cold.

498
00:34:18,549 --> 00:34:19,591
Let's do it here.

499
00:34:20,050 --> 00:34:21,843
It's that area. Zone F.

500
00:34:32,437 --> 00:34:33,438
Hey.

501
00:34:39,987 --> 00:34:41,613
- What's with you?
- Be quiet.

502
00:35:22,195 --> 00:35:23,530
DIRECTOR KIM HAN-SU

503
00:35:23,614 --> 00:35:25,157
<i>The president approved!</i>

504
00:35:25,240 --> 00:35:27,909
<i>You'll be out of the Audit Team</i>
<i>within days, Mr. Noh.</i>

505
00:35:27,993 --> 00:35:30,454
Director Kim, you're awesome!

506
00:35:34,124 --> 00:35:36,335
<i>I'm the best</i>

507
00:35:37,836 --> 00:35:39,588
<i>I'm the best</i>

508
00:35:40,881 --> 00:35:42,966
- Are you getting off early today?
- I'll try to.

509
00:35:43,300 --> 00:35:44,509
- Let's eat something good.
- Okay.

510
00:35:44,885 --> 00:35:46,803
- Try to clock out quickly.
- Okay.

511
00:35:51,642 --> 00:35:54,019
- Hello. Good morning.
- Hello.

512
00:35:59,149 --> 00:36:01,401
- The weather's great, isn't it?
- Yes.

513
00:36:02,319 --> 00:36:04,946
You're looking extra sharp today.

514
00:36:05,656 --> 00:36:06,865
- Do I?
- Yes.

515
00:36:07,616 --> 00:36:09,576
You two look great, too.

516
00:36:10,911 --> 00:36:12,329
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

517
00:36:24,800 --> 00:36:25,801
Hello, Ms. Joo.

518
00:36:26,385 --> 00:36:27,844
Hey, Mr. Noh. Good morning.

519
00:36:28,303 --> 00:36:30,639
You must like dress shirts.
You look good in them.

520
00:36:32,724 --> 00:36:33,934
You're looking happy.

521
00:36:34,393 --> 00:36:35,936
Did something great happen
this morning?

522
00:36:36,186 --> 00:36:38,105
There's no reason
to be in a foul mood.

523
00:36:38,188 --> 00:36:39,523
Look at that great weather.

524
00:36:39,606 --> 00:36:40,982
There is a reason, actually.

525
00:36:42,067 --> 00:36:44,194
You haven't caught
a single case in the parking garage.

526
00:36:45,320 --> 00:36:47,656
You won't take matters lightly
just like you did

527
00:36:47,739 --> 00:36:49,366
with Mr. Son's case, will you?

528
00:36:50,534 --> 00:36:51,576
Keep it up, will you?

529
00:36:51,660 --> 00:36:54,454
Every assignment is important
here in the Audit Team.

530
00:36:55,539 --> 00:36:58,750
<i>Fine, I'll go along. I won't have</i>
<i>to see her for much longer.</i>

531
00:36:59,042 --> 00:37:00,335
Yes, of course.

532
00:37:00,627 --> 00:37:02,963
I even brought my car
to stake out properly.

533
00:37:03,422 --> 00:37:05,048
Will I ever let you down again?

534
00:37:06,174 --> 00:37:07,342
No, never.

535
00:37:15,684 --> 00:37:16,768
Ms. Joo.

536
00:37:17,144 --> 00:37:20,230
There was a huge lucky draw
at our online mall recently

537
00:37:20,439 --> 00:37:23,024
and people are asking
how the winners were decided

538
00:37:23,108 --> 00:37:25,235
or if the draw was even real,
and some are complaining

539
00:37:25,318 --> 00:37:27,070
that they didn't win
even after many tries.

540
00:37:27,154 --> 00:37:29,865
It's not like the Audit Team
is the customer service center.

541
00:37:29,948 --> 00:37:32,701
Mr. Noh, you can continue
to work on the parking lot case.

542
00:37:33,034 --> 00:37:34,286
Wait a second.

543
00:37:34,745 --> 00:37:36,997
You'll need a partner
for your stakeout, won't you?

544
00:37:37,706 --> 00:37:39,583
Goodness. One second.

545
00:37:40,500 --> 00:37:43,128
White Blood Cell is on the phone too.
We don't have enough manpower.

546
00:37:44,713 --> 00:37:46,298
We do, Mr. Moo.

547
00:37:46,965 --> 00:37:48,633
We have our strongest asset here.

548
00:37:50,510 --> 00:37:51,511
Who?

549
00:37:59,770 --> 00:38:01,563
You're making me feel uncomfortable.
Cut it out.

550
00:38:03,982 --> 00:38:07,110
Why? Is the parking lot case
not quite suitable for you?

551
00:38:09,362 --> 00:38:12,657
But you told me that every case here
is equally important.

552
00:38:18,079 --> 00:38:19,247
Shall I do that, then?

553
00:38:19,998 --> 00:38:22,542
Let's spend some quality time alone.

554
00:38:30,801 --> 00:38:32,385
You don't need to buckle up.

555
00:38:33,261 --> 00:38:34,304
I'm not starting the car.

556
00:38:37,140 --> 00:38:38,266
It's my decision.

557
00:38:38,350 --> 00:38:40,060
Come on. You forgot, didn't you?

558
00:38:40,560 --> 00:38:42,270
Unbuckle it.
It must be uncomfortable.

559
00:38:42,354 --> 00:38:44,231
No, I'm not uncomfortable at all.

560
00:38:44,314 --> 00:38:46,358
I feel so comfortable right now.

561
00:38:46,441 --> 00:38:48,610
Unbuckle it. You don't need
to play it cool over this matter.

562
00:38:50,821 --> 00:38:52,155
Things happen.

563
00:38:52,531 --> 00:38:55,450
Stakeouts are for people
who are experienced.

564
00:38:55,659 --> 00:38:56,868
It's all right.

565
00:38:59,204 --> 00:39:02,791
I knew it. Your understanding
of these assignments is very high.

566
00:39:02,874 --> 00:39:03,875
Sorry?

567
00:39:05,126 --> 00:39:07,003
I'm sure you know a thing or two

568
00:39:07,087 --> 00:39:09,422
about cases like this one.

569
00:39:12,801 --> 00:39:13,844
Ms. Joo.

570
00:39:14,553 --> 00:39:17,681
- Back then, that...
- That? What do you mean by that?

571
00:39:17,764 --> 00:39:19,975
That. Whatever it is you saw.

572
00:39:20,350 --> 00:39:21,393
It wasn't that...

573
00:39:21,977 --> 00:39:24,271
I'm not that kind of person.

574
00:39:24,521 --> 00:39:26,314
My lips were also...

575
00:39:27,399 --> 00:39:28,441
Quiet.

576
00:39:29,901 --> 00:39:30,944
Over there.

577
00:39:55,135 --> 00:39:56,136
Okay.

578
00:40:11,067 --> 00:40:13,361
I'll wrap it up. It's my job.

579
00:40:25,790 --> 00:40:28,043
I'll open the door.
I'm from the Audit Team.

580
00:40:37,010 --> 00:40:38,553
I'm opening the door.

581
00:40:46,311 --> 00:40:48,647
Oh, my. Director Kim!

582
00:40:49,147 --> 00:40:50,273
You said you were busy.

583
00:40:52,943 --> 00:40:55,320
- Wait.
- What are you two doing here?

584
00:40:55,403 --> 00:40:56,404
What's with you?

585
00:40:57,739 --> 00:41:00,200
You, of all people,
should know better.

586
00:41:00,283 --> 00:41:03,203
When you both have spouses,
don't you?

587
00:41:06,331 --> 00:41:08,625
Will you close that door?

588
00:41:09,668 --> 00:41:11,169
Wrap it up and come outside.

589
00:41:19,928 --> 00:41:21,388
I knew it, Mr. Noh.

590
00:41:21,638 --> 00:41:23,556
I knew you could do it!

591
00:41:24,140 --> 00:41:27,352
You caught a big one.
He's a big fish!

592
00:41:27,852 --> 00:41:30,021
This is why you're the ace
of the Audit Team.

593
00:41:31,189 --> 00:41:32,232
Let's see.

594
00:41:32,565 --> 00:41:35,944
Director Kim was
formerly your direct superior.

595
00:41:38,279 --> 00:41:41,116
You took down your former superior
whom you worked with for years

596
00:41:41,783 --> 00:41:43,618
like a cold-blooded man!

597
00:41:44,285 --> 00:41:45,912
If only everyone else were like you

598
00:41:45,996 --> 00:41:49,749
this world would've been
a much better place.

599
00:41:57,215 --> 00:41:58,466
Excuse me, Ms. Joo.

600
00:41:59,009 --> 00:42:01,761
Is there a possibility
that Director Kim will be let off

601
00:42:01,845 --> 00:42:04,180
- just like Mr. Son?
- No.

602
00:42:04,597 --> 00:42:06,474
This is a different case.

603
00:42:07,058 --> 00:42:09,602
He's an executive, so we can revoke
his contract and fire him right away.

604
00:42:09,686 --> 00:42:11,021
Fire him?

605
00:42:12,022 --> 00:42:14,607
But Director Kim is also
a necessary part of the company...

606
00:42:14,691 --> 00:42:16,109
Not at all.

607
00:42:16,443 --> 00:42:18,570
He's an old-timer with an ego
who sits around doing nothing

608
00:42:18,653 --> 00:42:20,030
only because
he's close to the president.

609
00:42:20,864 --> 00:42:22,615
He must've been an eyesore
to the vice president.

610
00:42:23,867 --> 00:42:27,454
You just gave him
a wonderful reason to fire that man.

611
00:42:32,792 --> 00:42:33,918
Director Kim

612
00:42:36,296 --> 00:42:37,297
is done for.

613
00:43:06,034 --> 00:43:08,411
DIRECTOR KIM HAN-SU

614
00:43:11,122 --> 00:43:13,917
<i>Your call cannot be connected.</i>
<i>You will be redirected to...</i>

615
00:43:26,054 --> 00:43:28,848
ELDEST SISTER
ACCEPT

616
00:43:28,932 --> 00:43:30,600
- <i>Hilarious.</i>
- Hey.

617
00:43:31,142 --> 00:43:33,978
<i>Hello, Ki-jun? When are you coming?</i>

618
00:43:34,771 --> 00:43:36,731
I'm on my way, and I'm almost there.

619
00:43:41,277 --> 00:43:44,155
Ki-jun, we have to change
the bathroom doorknob, too.

620
00:43:44,447 --> 00:43:45,490
Okay.

621
00:43:47,117 --> 00:43:48,159
Hey, Ki-jun!

622
00:43:48,576 --> 00:43:50,370
Take a look at Jin-yeong's laptop.

623
00:43:50,954 --> 00:43:52,664
- Laptop?
- Hey, Ki-jun.

624
00:43:52,747 --> 00:43:54,249
That couch has been wobbling.
Take a look.

625
00:43:54,624 --> 00:43:57,460
I'm only one man,
so talk to me one at a time.

626
00:43:59,170 --> 00:44:00,171
The couch?

627
00:44:02,215 --> 00:44:04,008
- Which side is wobbly?
- The left.

628
00:44:04,092 --> 00:44:05,343
Goodness.

629
00:44:07,470 --> 00:44:11,099
Goodness, I'm so proud of you,
my youngest one.

630
00:44:13,768 --> 00:44:15,728
Cut it out, Mom.

631
00:44:21,985 --> 00:44:23,528
Mom, this meat is delicious.

632
00:44:27,157 --> 00:44:29,075
Hey, Ki-jun.
Why are you drinking so much?

633
00:44:29,159 --> 00:44:30,910
Look at him.
He hasn't even eaten his food.

634
00:44:30,994 --> 00:44:32,245
You can't even hold your alcohol.

635
00:44:33,413 --> 00:44:36,291
- Stop drinking.
- Stop pinching me, please!

636
00:44:37,000 --> 00:44:38,293
Will you just leave me alone?

637
00:44:38,376 --> 00:44:39,878
Is something going on, Ki-jun?

638
00:44:40,128 --> 00:44:41,421
Right? What's wrong?

639
00:44:42,088 --> 00:44:43,715
Hey, is someone bullying you?

640
00:44:44,757 --> 00:44:47,635
What? Hey, who is it?
Who's that punk?

641
00:44:47,719 --> 00:44:49,596
Hey, go file a lawsuit.

642
00:44:49,679 --> 00:44:51,347
- Talk to her husband!
- I'll talk to him.

643
00:44:51,431 --> 00:44:53,391
We have to talk it out first.
Do you want me to make a call?

644
00:44:53,474 --> 00:44:55,894
Please stop this and leave me alone.

645
00:44:55,977 --> 00:44:57,896
We need the name first. Who is it?

646
00:44:57,979 --> 00:45:00,023
- We have to talk it out first.
- Talk what out?

647
00:45:00,106 --> 00:45:01,900
Look at this kid.

648
00:45:01,983 --> 00:45:04,194
Call your husband first, okay?

649
00:45:04,277 --> 00:45:07,322
Who's the punk that did this
to my precious son?

650
00:45:08,031 --> 00:45:09,324
- You...
- Darn it.

651
00:45:09,407 --> 00:45:10,742
- Who is it?
- Talk it out.

652
00:45:10,825 --> 00:45:12,827
- Hey, tell me who it is.
- We need the name first.

653
00:45:12,911 --> 00:45:14,787
- What's the name?
- Mom, listen.

654
00:45:14,871 --> 00:45:16,956
- We need the name first.
- We need that.

655
00:45:17,040 --> 00:45:18,291
- Who is it?
- Why won't he pick up?

656
00:45:18,374 --> 00:45:19,667
- Get the name.
- We need the name.

657
00:45:19,751 --> 00:45:21,127
You all need to stop.

658
00:45:21,211 --> 00:45:23,004
- Who is it? Tell me!
- Hear me out.

659
00:45:23,087 --> 00:45:25,882
- Ki-jun.
- I hate all three of you!

660
00:45:25,965 --> 00:45:28,218
Just leave me alone!

661
00:45:28,301 --> 00:45:30,720
No, bring her phone to me.

662
00:45:30,929 --> 00:45:33,139
- Is he not picking up?
- Call the customer service line.

663
00:45:33,223 --> 00:45:35,725
- The customer service?
- We need to reach someone!

664
00:45:50,865 --> 00:45:53,076
HAEMU PHARMACEUTICAL
2025 CONTRACT INSPECTION

665
00:45:53,159 --> 00:45:54,869
2024 FUND EXECUTION INSPECTION

666
00:45:58,248 --> 00:45:59,916
NOH KI-JUN, AUDIT TEAM 1 TURNOVER

667
00:45:59,999 --> 00:46:04,712
DO YOU WISH TO PERMANENTLY DELETE
ALL FOLDERS AND FILES?

668
00:46:24,482 --> 00:46:27,026
I'm sorry about Director Kim.

669
00:46:27,110 --> 00:46:29,195
- Did you dig him up intentionally?
- No.

670
00:46:30,154 --> 00:46:31,614
It was a coincidence
from another case.

671
00:46:31,698 --> 00:46:32,699
How disappointing.

672
00:46:32,991 --> 00:46:34,701
I thought you finally learned
to wield your sword

673
00:46:34,784 --> 00:46:35,910
but it was sheer luck.

674
00:46:37,203 --> 00:46:39,080
I haven't given you anything yet.

675
00:46:39,747 --> 00:46:40,790
Prove yourself

676
00:46:41,499 --> 00:46:42,792
that you're different from your mom.

677
00:47:06,524 --> 00:47:08,818
Honey, Sung-yeol is here.

678
00:47:10,194 --> 00:47:12,405
You should say hi to him.
I'll go and make coffee.

679
00:47:15,199 --> 00:47:17,035
Father, your youngest son is here.

680
00:47:18,703 --> 00:47:21,372
- And so are you, Jae-yeol.
- It's been a while.

681
00:47:23,833 --> 00:47:25,168
How's your health, Father?

682
00:47:25,710 --> 00:47:27,879
I've exiled you
and haven't called you back.

683
00:47:28,296 --> 00:47:29,922
How dare you show yourself here?

684
00:47:30,006 --> 00:47:31,632
It's great to see
that you're the same.

685
00:47:34,344 --> 00:47:36,429
How come there is
no middle ground between you two?

686
00:47:36,846 --> 00:47:39,182
One of you is too soft
to do anything substantial

687
00:47:39,515 --> 00:47:43,019
and the other is too reckless,
causing trouble everywhere.

688
00:47:43,436 --> 00:47:44,437
Darn it.

689
00:47:46,022 --> 00:47:48,149
You see, Father

690
00:47:49,150 --> 00:47:50,651
I have caused yet another trouble.

691
00:47:52,362 --> 00:47:54,864
It's the gas plant in Saudi Arabia
that you've even dreamed of.

692
00:47:54,947 --> 00:47:57,950
I got the first package,
and on top of that the third one.

693
00:47:58,284 --> 00:48:00,995
The entire project
is worth 8.77 billion dollars.

694
00:48:01,913 --> 00:48:03,039
And I got it.

695
00:48:10,254 --> 00:48:13,174
So? Isn't this good enough
to put an end to my exile?

696
00:48:14,509 --> 00:48:16,469
I hear there's a spot open
in the head office.

697
00:48:32,860 --> 00:48:34,195
Should I cancel the luncheon?

698
00:48:34,570 --> 00:48:36,030
You do not look well.

699
00:48:37,281 --> 00:48:38,324
I'm fine.

700
00:48:40,910 --> 00:48:42,870
I need personnel evaluation reports

701
00:48:43,371 --> 00:48:45,081
and a list of potential staff
up for a promotion.

702
00:48:45,873 --> 00:48:46,916
Also, set up

703
00:48:47,458 --> 00:48:50,378
a dinner with QS International's
President Lee Hyeong-geun

704
00:48:50,753 --> 00:48:51,754
as soon as possible.

705
00:48:52,296 --> 00:48:53,506
I understand.

706
00:48:54,799 --> 00:48:57,301
Would you like to leave right away
for the AI camp?

707
00:48:58,386 --> 00:48:59,387
In half an hour.

708
00:49:01,722 --> 00:49:02,807
One second.

709
00:49:24,912 --> 00:49:26,372
I can do this for myself.

710
00:49:27,999 --> 00:49:29,167
E-mail me the files.

711
00:49:32,753 --> 00:49:33,754
Yes, sir.

712
00:50:11,667 --> 00:50:14,045
- What now?
- I'm telling you.

713
00:50:17,256 --> 00:50:18,799
Goodness, I need some sugar.

714
00:50:21,761 --> 00:50:22,762
My gosh.

715
00:50:24,680 --> 00:50:27,642
Where was Ms. Yoon's snack box again?

716
00:50:29,143 --> 00:50:31,145
There it is. Ms. Yoon's snack box.

717
00:50:32,313 --> 00:50:35,483
Goodness. It's heavy.
Did you get something new?

718
00:50:36,859 --> 00:50:38,444
Hey, these are new.

719
00:50:42,573 --> 00:50:43,574
It's good.

720
00:50:44,909 --> 00:50:45,952
- Mango-flavored?
- Yes.

721
00:50:46,285 --> 00:50:48,704
Hey, Hae-young. Where are we
having team dinner again?

722
00:50:48,788 --> 00:50:50,248
Piggy's Charcoal BBQ.

723
00:50:50,331 --> 00:50:51,332
We're having pork again?

724
00:50:51,832 --> 00:50:54,502
Can we get something better?
It's Ms. Joo's welcome party.

725
00:50:54,585 --> 00:50:56,879
Our budget for team dinners
is running low this year.

726
00:50:57,171 --> 00:50:58,631
Ms. Pyun.

727
00:50:59,048 --> 00:51:01,217
Why do you act like
a stingy mother-in-law

728
00:51:01,300 --> 00:51:04,053
who never lets anyone near her money
with the company fund?

729
00:51:05,179 --> 00:51:07,348
There's a servant
that's trying to clean out the fund

730
00:51:07,682 --> 00:51:09,016
so I have no other choice, Mr. Moo.

731
00:51:09,100 --> 00:51:10,101
- What?
- Servant?

732
00:51:10,434 --> 00:51:11,477
You heard her, right?

733
00:51:11,561 --> 00:51:13,020
Did you just call me a servant?

734
00:51:13,104 --> 00:51:15,773
- Do you feel guilty?
- Technically, we're all servants.

735
00:51:16,774 --> 00:51:17,858
Anyway.

736
00:51:18,442 --> 00:51:20,069
Where's Mr. Noh?
He's been away for a while.

737
00:51:20,152 --> 00:51:22,613
Mr. Noh didn't seem well.

738
00:51:22,697 --> 00:51:25,491
He doesn't look well,
he keeps sighing

739
00:51:25,866 --> 00:51:28,536
and his eyes looked a bit watery too.

740
00:51:29,120 --> 00:51:31,539
- Anyway, he looks quite sad.
- Really?

741
00:51:32,623 --> 00:51:34,792
- Did he get dumped?
- I think so.

742
00:51:34,875 --> 00:51:37,003
Goodness. That's heartbreaking.

743
00:51:41,549 --> 00:51:42,925
Thanks a lot.

744
00:52:03,195 --> 00:52:04,238
<i>He is</i>

745
00:52:04,864 --> 00:52:05,948
<i>leaving.</i>

746
00:52:11,621 --> 00:52:12,747
<i>My hope.</i>

747
00:52:14,123 --> 00:52:15,333
<i>My lifeline.</i>

748
00:52:18,336 --> 00:52:19,462
Adios.

749
00:52:20,838 --> 00:52:22,465
PIGGY'S CHARCOAL BBQ

750
00:52:22,548 --> 00:52:23,549
Hello.

751
00:52:23,758 --> 00:52:24,925
Thank you.

752
00:52:31,307 --> 00:52:33,726
It used to be a great spot.

753
00:52:34,727 --> 00:52:36,729
Back then, the front of the factory
used to be salt farms.

754
00:52:36,812 --> 00:52:38,481
It became a huge issue.

755
00:52:38,564 --> 00:52:40,816
What's the most important
when it comes to making salt?

756
00:52:40,900 --> 00:52:41,984
Sunlight and wind.

757
00:52:42,652 --> 00:52:44,612
So if the southeastern direction
gets blocked off

758
00:52:45,154 --> 00:52:47,490
it creates a shadow
and stops the wind

759
00:52:47,573 --> 00:52:48,866
which stops salt from crystallizing.

760
00:52:49,533 --> 00:52:52,620
And the one who stepped up
as a troubleshooter was...

761
00:52:52,703 --> 00:52:53,788
Mr. Baek.

762
00:52:54,413 --> 00:52:57,375
- You should eat some, too.
- I've been eating. It's okay.

763
00:52:57,583 --> 00:53:00,836
You're making me look rude.

764
00:53:00,920 --> 00:53:02,129
After all, I'm the youngest.

765
00:53:03,798 --> 00:53:05,466
No, it's all right, really.

766
00:53:05,925 --> 00:53:08,511
Because everyone thinks
you're just like that.

767
00:53:08,594 --> 00:53:09,887
That I'm just rude?

768
00:53:11,639 --> 00:53:12,723
That wasn't what I meant.

769
00:53:13,891 --> 00:53:15,559
The meat is burning. Have some.

770
00:53:16,102 --> 00:53:18,854
- And Mr. Oh is such an odd guy.
- You just dissed me.

771
00:53:18,938 --> 00:53:22,066
This happened during the early days
of his time in China.

772
00:53:22,149 --> 00:53:23,150
Really?

773
00:53:23,901 --> 00:53:25,611
What do you mean?
I haven't said anything.

774
00:53:25,695 --> 00:53:27,738
- I can't believe it.
- Wait, it's not that.

775
00:53:27,947 --> 00:53:30,157
Will you listen up?
Anyway, this guy...

776
00:53:30,700 --> 00:53:31,867
All right.

777
00:53:32,076 --> 00:53:34,870
Audit Team Three,
why don't we make a toast?

778
00:53:34,954 --> 00:53:36,664
Hello, Ms. Joo.

779
00:53:37,498 --> 00:53:38,791
Thank you.

780
00:53:39,792 --> 00:53:42,878
- Shall we have a toast?
- One second, please.

781
00:53:43,170 --> 00:53:44,255
Goodness.

782
00:53:45,423 --> 00:53:47,258
- Yes, drink up.
- I will.

783
00:53:47,341 --> 00:53:48,968
We're all here
to make a living, aren't we?

784
00:53:49,051 --> 00:53:50,344
- Thank you.
- Sure.

785
00:53:50,970 --> 00:53:53,097
- Now, would you like a drink?
- Yes, Ms. Joo.

786
00:53:53,264 --> 00:53:55,307
- Drink up.
- Thank you.

787
00:53:59,311 --> 00:54:01,063
Mr. Noh, why don't you
have a drink, too?

788
00:54:08,112 --> 00:54:09,405
You want soju?

789
00:54:10,072 --> 00:54:11,115
Okay.

790
00:54:12,324 --> 00:54:14,827
You've done well, Mr. Noh.

791
00:54:17,329 --> 00:54:19,749
You all know
that Mr. Noh got someone big, right?

792
00:54:19,832 --> 00:54:20,833
Yes, of course.

793
00:54:20,916 --> 00:54:22,668
Mr. Noh is the pride of our team!

794
00:54:22,752 --> 00:54:25,504
He says you're the pride.

795
00:54:26,255 --> 00:54:28,507
Why don't we make a toast to Mr. Noh,
the ace of Audit Team Three?

796
00:54:28,799 --> 00:54:30,426
- Shall we?
- Goodness.

797
00:54:30,509 --> 00:54:31,719
All right.

798
00:54:32,470 --> 00:54:34,388
To Mr. Noh.

799
00:54:34,472 --> 00:54:36,515
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

800
00:54:36,599 --> 00:54:38,476
- Cheers!
- All right, Mr. Noh!

801
00:54:41,103 --> 00:54:42,396
That's nice.

802
00:54:43,314 --> 00:54:44,315
Gosh.

803
00:54:45,107 --> 00:54:47,109
That's a nice drink.

804
00:54:47,818 --> 00:54:48,861
May I?

805
00:54:50,154 --> 00:54:51,197
A lettuce wrap, Ms. Joo.

806
00:54:51,280 --> 00:54:54,325
<i>I need you baby, bye bye bye</i>

807
00:54:54,408 --> 00:54:57,995
<i>Must you go, why why why?</i>

808
00:54:58,078 --> 00:55:00,915
<i>All you said was a lie lie lie</i>

809
00:55:00,998 --> 00:55:03,834
<i>I will wait</i>

810
00:55:03,918 --> 00:55:07,421
<i>Until the day I die</i>

811
00:55:07,922 --> 00:55:13,093
<i>Do not cry alone</i>
<i>Because I am not there</i>

812
00:55:14,136 --> 00:55:16,680
<i>Goodbye</i>

813
00:55:19,892 --> 00:55:22,937
<i>Come back</i>

814
00:55:23,020 --> 00:55:26,816
<i>My dear</i>

815
00:55:27,900 --> 00:55:31,445
<i>Do you not know</i>

816
00:55:32,071 --> 00:55:34,114
- These songs are killing the vibe.
- Right?

817
00:55:35,658 --> 00:55:39,119
May I resuscitate the mood
as the head of this organization?

818
00:55:41,080 --> 00:55:42,957
Drop that microphone now.

819
00:55:44,124 --> 00:55:46,210
Come back here, Mr. Noh.

820
00:55:46,877 --> 00:55:49,171
It's "Twit"!

821
00:55:49,255 --> 00:55:50,256
Okay!

822
00:55:59,348 --> 00:56:00,808
<i>You're a fool</i>

823
00:56:01,934 --> 00:56:03,853
- Twit, twit, twit, twit!
- Twit, twit, twit, twit!

824
00:56:03,936 --> 00:56:05,187
<i>I don't like it</i>

825
00:56:05,271 --> 00:56:07,857
<i>Nobody likes it</i>
<i>The delicate Sim Cheong</i>

826
00:56:08,983 --> 00:56:10,985
- Twit, twit, twit, twit!
- Twit, twit, twit, twit!

827
00:56:11,068 --> 00:56:13,863
<i>I don't like it</i>
<i>Nobody likes it</i>

828
00:56:14,196 --> 00:56:15,614
<i>You're a fool</i>

829
00:56:16,615 --> 00:56:18,826
<i>All you care about is yourself</i>

830
00:56:19,910 --> 00:56:23,414
<i>The delicate Sim Cheong</i>

831
00:56:23,622 --> 00:56:24,874
<i>Try to look around</i>

832
00:56:25,583 --> 00:56:28,419
<i>You're in pain but you have no idea</i>

833
00:56:28,878 --> 00:56:30,546
<i>You make me royal</i>
<i>You make me a hero</i>

834
00:56:30,629 --> 00:56:31,964
<i>You make me a genius, yes</i>

835
00:56:32,256 --> 00:56:35,509
<i>You give a lot</i>
<i>But why do you always end up unhappy?</i>

836
00:56:35,885 --> 00:56:39,096
<i>Because you only breathe for yourself</i>

837
00:56:41,640 --> 00:56:43,100
<i>You're a fool</i>

838
00:56:43,183 --> 00:56:46,186
- Yeah! Twit, twit, twit, twit!
- Twit, twit, twit, twit!

839
00:56:46,270 --> 00:56:49,315
<i>I don't like it</i>
<i>Nobody likes it</i>

840
00:56:55,154 --> 00:56:56,363
Ms. Joo In-a.

841
00:56:57,489 --> 00:56:59,325
Don't you think this is too much?

842
00:57:06,415 --> 00:57:07,416
Fine.

843
00:57:08,250 --> 00:57:09,877
I kissed.

844
00:57:11,503 --> 00:57:14,214
I know that's why you put me
in charge of PM.

845
00:57:15,466 --> 00:57:16,967
But what's so bad about that?

846
00:57:17,968 --> 00:57:21,555
Why is that misconduct?

847
00:57:23,015 --> 00:57:24,642
Does anyone here never kiss?

848
00:57:25,601 --> 00:57:26,644
Ever?

849
00:57:26,727 --> 00:57:28,812
Don't you ever kiss?

850
00:57:29,229 --> 00:57:31,231
Don't you kiss, too?

851
00:58:24,493 --> 00:58:25,536
Are you okay?

852
00:58:25,911 --> 00:58:27,121
You threw up all night.

853
00:58:29,581 --> 00:58:30,874
I heard
you dropped a bomb last night.

854
00:58:31,500 --> 00:58:32,751
How did you know?

855
00:58:32,835 --> 00:58:34,169
We are a company.

856
00:58:34,253 --> 00:58:36,338
Something fun like that
goes around in real-time.

857
00:58:37,923 --> 00:58:39,842
You've never been
the object of hatred, have you?

858
00:58:40,217 --> 00:58:42,845
You're the beloved Noh Ki-jun,
whom everyone liked.

859
00:58:43,429 --> 00:58:44,596
Beloved, my foot.

860
00:58:50,519 --> 00:58:52,229
After all, it's just work.

861
00:58:52,980 --> 00:58:55,065
She'll forget someday
if I do my job well, right?

862
00:58:55,691 --> 00:58:56,692
Ki-jun.

863
00:58:57,192 --> 00:59:00,279
When you adore someone,
you adore them for no reason.

864
00:59:00,362 --> 00:59:03,407
But once you hate someone,
you hate them no matter what they do.

865
00:59:04,241 --> 00:59:07,369
I'm sure Ms. Joo thinks
you're her biggest eyesore right now

866
00:59:07,453 --> 00:59:08,454
no matter what you do.

867
00:59:09,663 --> 00:59:11,248
Should I just quit?

868
00:59:11,331 --> 00:59:13,167
You still need to get to work

869
00:59:13,709 --> 00:59:15,335
to turn in your resignation.

870
00:59:16,211 --> 00:59:17,379
I'm taking the day off.

871
00:59:18,338 --> 00:59:19,381
Good for you.

872
00:59:39,193 --> 00:59:40,611
Excuse me, Ms. Joo.

873
00:59:41,779 --> 00:59:43,113
I apologize for last night.

874
00:59:43,322 --> 00:59:44,782
You must've been quite disappointed.

875
00:59:45,616 --> 00:59:46,617
Sorry?

876
00:59:49,578 --> 00:59:52,081
That you couldn't transfer
to General Business Control HQ.

877
00:59:55,334 --> 00:59:58,462
You should've talked to me
if you wanted to leave the team.

878
00:59:58,545 --> 01:00:00,089
I'm not that uptight.

879
01:00:01,006 --> 01:00:02,466
Instead of talking behind my back.

880
01:00:04,593 --> 01:00:07,429
Also, that department
is no longer in formation

881
01:00:07,513 --> 01:00:08,722
with Director Kim's dismissal.

882
01:00:18,732 --> 01:00:20,818
Are you feeling all right?

883
01:00:21,735 --> 01:00:23,237
I think

884
01:00:23,529 --> 01:00:26,031
you're really something, Mr. Noh.

885
01:00:26,240 --> 01:00:28,200
If I were you,
I could never come to work.

886
01:00:28,534 --> 01:00:30,452
Stop making matters worse.

887
01:00:31,411 --> 01:00:34,123
I'm sure it's hard enough for him.

888
01:00:34,373 --> 01:00:35,415
Isn't it?

889
01:00:38,127 --> 01:00:39,920
I guess he's the type who blows up.

890
01:00:48,804 --> 01:00:51,140
No, okay? That's not it.

891
01:01:03,110 --> 01:01:04,111
NOH KI-JUN

892
01:01:05,237 --> 01:01:06,905
CHECK SEVERANCE PAY

893
01:01:07,823 --> 01:01:09,491
SEVERANCE PAY: 40,788,560 WON

894
01:01:09,575 --> 01:01:10,576
<i>All right.</i>

895
01:01:10,784 --> 01:01:13,453
<i>That's enough money</i>
<i>to last some time to get refreshed</i>

896
01:01:13,537 --> 01:01:14,955
<i>before I get another job.</i>

897
01:01:16,039 --> 01:01:17,791
<i>Dang it. I'll just quit.</i>

898
01:01:19,960 --> 01:01:21,003
LETTER OF RESIGNATION

899
01:01:22,754 --> 01:01:24,131
NAME: NOH KI-JUN

900
01:01:24,214 --> 01:01:25,465
REQUESTED BY: NOH KI-JUN

901
01:01:38,145 --> 01:01:39,438
LETTER OF RESIGNATION

902
01:01:57,331 --> 01:01:58,957
Ms. Joo, I must talk to you.

903
01:02:01,460 --> 01:02:02,502
Mr. Noh.

904
01:02:02,920 --> 01:02:03,962
Mr. Noh!

905
01:02:07,341 --> 01:02:08,759
